# /etc/fw_env.config — U-Boot environment access configuration
# Used by fw_printenv / fw_setenv (libubootenv-tool package)
#
# Mono Gateway LS1046A: U-Boot env stored in SPI NOR flash (QSPI)
# DTS partition "uboot-env" = mtd2
#
# Format: Device   Offset   Env_size   Sector_size
# - Offset: 0x0 = start of the MTD partition (not flash absolute offset)
# - Env_size: 0x2000 (8 KB) — matches U-Boot CONFIG_ENV_SIZE
# - Sector_size: 0x1000 (4 KB) — QSPI NOR erase block from /proc/mtd
#
# Verified on live hardware 2026-04-03:
#   /proc/mtd shows: mtd0=rcw-bl2, mtd1=uboot, mtd2=uboot-env, mtd3=fman-ucode
#   Previous builds had mtd3=uboot-env (partition numbering changed)
#   brute-force test confirmed only 0x2000 produces valid CRC
#   hexdump /dev/mtd2 shows CRC + ASCII key=value (arch=arm, bootcmd=...)
#
/dev/mtd2	0x0	0x2000	0x1000